The throttle is the in-memory variable at `server/services/getService.js:849-850`:

```js
let _lastHottestCheckTime = 0;
const HOTTEST_CHECK_INTERVAL_MS = 5 * 60 * 1000;
```

It's checked at the top of `updateHottestTrackerIfChanged` (line 853-856):

```js
const now = Date.now();
if(now - _lastHottestCheckTime < HOTTEST_CHECK_INTERVAL_MS){
    return;  // skips everything if <5 min since last check
}
_lastHottestCheckTime = now;
```

To verify it's working, add a temporary log:

```js
const now = Date.now();
if(now - _lastHottestCheckTime < HOTTEST_CHECK_INTERVAL_MS){
    console.log('hottest tracker: throttled, skipping');
    return;
}
_lastHottestCheckTime = now;
console.log('hottest tracker: running check');
```

Then refresh the Explore page a few times — you should see "running check" once, then "throttled, skipping" on subsequent refreshes. Remove the logs when done.

